2 unit Scallions
10 ounce Ground Beef
4 ounce Shredded Red Cabbage
2 tablespoon Szechuan Paste
4 tablespoon Sweet Soy Glaze
1 unit Beef Stock Concentrate
6 ounce Ramen Noodles
1 tablespoon Sesame Seeds
Salt
1 teaspoon Cooking Oil
1 teaspoon Sugar
1 tablespoon Butter

• Bring a medium pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and
dry produce.
• Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites
from greens.

• Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add beef*; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
browned and cooked through, 4-6 minutes. TIP: If there’s
excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.
• Stir in scallion whites and cabbage; cook until tender,
2-3 minutes.

• Stir in Szechuan paste, sweet soy glaze, stock
concentrate, and 1 tsp sugar (2 tsp for 4 servings). Cook,
stirring, until beef mixture is thoroughly coated in sauce.
• Reduce heat to low.

• Once water is boiling, add ²⁄3 of the noodles (save the rest
for another use) to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
tender, 1-2 minutes. Drain and thoroughly rinse under
cold water for at least 30 seconds. (This stops the cooking
and helps prevent sticky noodles.)
• Add drained noodles and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for
4 servings) to pan with beef mixture; toss until noodles are
warmed through and everything is combined, 1-2 minutes.
TIP: If needed, add water a splash at a time until noodles
are thoroughly coated in sauce.
• Divide between bowls and top with scallion greens and
a pinch of sesame seeds. Serve.